Seven antitrust lawsuits which
were filed against electrical
equipment manufacturers by the
Salt River Project in 1861, were
dismissed in federal court here.


Project President, Victor |.
Corbell, said the cases we're dis
missed because adequate settle
ment has been made with the COM
panies involved outside the court.
The suits were filed In the wake
of antitrust law violations. which
were disclosed by the United
States Justice Department in
1861.

Settlements reached with the
companies are estimated to be
about Sl.2 million. Corbell said
collection of the damages was
anticipated and taken into con-
sideration last October, when the
Project announced 1t was raising
electric rates In order to make
voluntary contributions in lieu
of taxes to state and local gov
ernments and school districts. He
said the settlements actually
helped hold down the rate increase
which was put into effect at that
time.

Corp. has agreed to a federal
court order banning interstate
sale of Regimen weight-reducing
tablets.


U. S. Atty. Joseph R. Hooey
charged that the tablets we're
worthless. He said the public
paid SIG million for them in the
past six years.


President John T. Andreadis
of Drug Research signed a gov
eminent decree in U.S.District
Court, Brooklyn, agreeing to ac-
cept Judge John r. Bartels in
junction.

The Phoenix Human Relations
Commission voted to begin pro-
gram designed to learn the kinds
and extents of racial discrim-
ination in the city.


The commission was unable to
decide whether 1t would openly
support the proposed state public
accommodation law.


1t agreed to cosponsor with the
National Conference of Christ
ians and Jews programs aiding
the observance of National Broth
erhood Week starting on Feb. g.


The commission will sponsor
a workshop for pers onnel direc-
tors to assist them in techniques
for aiding minority group inte-
grafton in employment.


Also, the commission will CO.
sponsor an Employment Integral
ton Conference with the NCCJ
on Feb. 6.


1t will ask City Manager Sam
Vickers about city employment
practices and minority group in
tegration.

ing of iron stains? You can usu-

recommend what you need ac-

water. If the iron content isn't
too high, water softener will
remove the iron. High concentra-
